caption: Table 1: The results of OpenAI's o1 model, GPT40, and some Test-time Compute methods on our selected four benchmarks (i.e., HotpotQA, Collie, USACO, AIME). The '-' in the table represents that the method does not search the multiple responses for generation. Direct refers to having the LLMs generate a response directly from the input text, while Test-Time refers to using the Test-time Compute method based on GPT-40.
description: Table 1 presents the performance comparison of OpenAI's o1 model, GPT-40, and several Test-time Compute methods on four benchmark datasets across commonsense reasoning, code, and math tasks.
